main event: A bright flash was observed in the sky near Annandale, Virginia on December 14, 1962 at 5:22 PM.
interesting points: The object appeared to be two objects converging into one.
The brightness of the object decreased after the initial bright flash.
The witness observed the object at the time of the sighting.
The sighting was estimated to last for 2 seconds.
The Air Force's analysis concluded that the sighting was probably a meteor, balloon, aircraft, or space debris, possibly an astronomical phenomenon.
sighted object: A single bright object in the sky
